message.content:
cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on artwork recognition using computer vision technologies. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the dataset consists of professional photographs of classic artworks. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper mentions instance retrieval as a focus of existing computer vision technologies in artwork recognition. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper mentions advancing the state-of-the-art in digital curation of museum collections through the iMet Collection 2019 Challenge. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions annotations being curated and verified by world-class museum experts, which could involve security measures to protect the authenticity of the annotations.
